# CSRD Testing Rules

## 1. Test files live ONLY under `tests/`

Allowed:
- `tests/unit/*Test.m`              - matlab.unittest classes for one block
- `tests/regression/test_*.m`       - top-level functions, end-to-end behaviour
- `tests/integration/*Test.m`       - matlab.unittest classes for cross-block flows

Forbidden:
- `test_*.m` in the repo root or anywhere outside `tests/`
- New files under `examples/` or `+csrd/` named `test_*`
- Stand-alone scripts that "smoke test" by side effect of being run

`tests/run_all_tests.m` discovers files automatically; do NOT hardcode test names in lists
that have to be edited every time a test is added.

## 2. Every fix MUST come with at least one test

If you patch a bug, write or extend a test that *would have failed before the patch*. Run the
test red first when feasible. The test must:
- live in the right directory (rule 1),
- name the bug it pins (in the comment header),
- exercise the production code path, not a re-implementation of the same logic.

## 3. Test must run the real code, not a re-implementation

```matlab
% BAD - test passes even if production swallows the exception
function runHarness()
    try
        error('CSRD:Channel:NoValidPaths', 'msg');
    catch ME
        if csrd.utils.scenario.isScenarioSkipException(ME)
            rethrow(ME);  % this is the test, NOT processChannelPropagation
        end
    end
end

% GOOD - real ChannelFactory + stub channel block
factory = csrd.factories.ChannelFactory('Config', cfg);  % cfg points handle at stub block
testCase.verifyError(@() step(factory, ...), 'RayTracing:NoValidPaths');
```

When real code is too heavy to spin up, supplement with a *static-text* assertion that the
production file calls the shared utility (e.g. `assert(contains(fileread(file), needle))`).

## 4. Run the suites before committing

Before any commit that touches `+csrd/` or `tests/`:

```matlab
results = run_all_tests('unit');         % seconds
results = run_all_tests('regression');   % minutes
% optionally: run_all_tests('all')
```

Both suites must report `Success=1`. If you have to disable a test, link the issue/plan
in the comment and remove the disable in the same commit that fixes the underlying problem.

## 5. Test-only support code goes under `+csrd/+test_support`

Stub channel blocks, throwing helpers, etc., live in `+csrd/+test_support`. Do not pollute
`+csrd/+blocks/` with classes only the test suite uses.
